  "CO₂ exists as discrete molecules held together by weak London dispersion forces, while NaCl is an ionic lattice and SiO₂ is a covalent network solid": "",
  "CO₂ has fewer electrons, making it lighter and easier to vaporize": "",
  "CO₂ is a molecular compound where individual molecules are held together by weak London dispersion forces. NaCl has strong ionic bonds in a lattice, and SiO₂ has a continuous covalent network, both requiring far more energy to break apart.": "",
  "A chemistry student must determine which Lewis structure of carbon monoxide (CO) is most stable. She draws three possibilities with different formal charge distributions. The actual bond in CO is a triple bond with a lone pair on each atom. What formal charges does this give carbon and oxygen?": "",
  "C = +1, O = -1": "",
