  "A materials scientist is developing new solar cell materials and considers using gallium arsenide (GaAs) instead of silicon. GaAs has bonds that are intermediate between ionic and covalent. Given that Ga has an electronegativity of 1.81 and As has 2.18, what best describes the bonding in GaAs?": "",
